article.headline: Sam leads Minnesota down the stretch
article.linkText: Lynx hand Indiana 2nd home loss this season
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (Ticker) -- Sheri Sam scored nine of her 20 points in the final four minutes as the Minnesota Lynx posted a 70-65 victory over the Indiana Fever, who suffered just their second home game of the season.

Indiana closed to 57-55 on two free throws by Tamika Catchings
with 4:57 left, but Sam scored Minnesota's next nine points.
Her 3-pointer gave the Lynx a 66-59 cushion with 1:57 to go.

Catchings paced Indiana with 20 points, including the 1,000th of
her career with 8:13 left in the first half.

Katie Smith scored 13 of her 21 points in the second half for
Minnesota, which has taken both meetings with Indiana this
season.

Smith, who has made a 3-pointer in a WNBA-record 30 straight
games, was 7-of-12 from the field, including 4-of-6 from beyond
the arc.

The Fever were trying to become the first WNBA team to win 10
home games but shot under 32 percent from the field (21-of-66)
and failed to take full advantage of 19 turnovers by the Lynx.

Minnesota shot 48 percent from the field (25-of-52), including
7-of-15 from 3-point range.  Indiana converted just 3-of-22
3-pointers.
